16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Economic Development
19 SUBTITLE 4E. MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE.
20 10–4E–01.
21 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
22 INDICATED.
23 (B) “CORPORATION” MEANS THE MARYLAND TECHNOLOGY
24 DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION.
25 (C) “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE FUND.
26 (D) “INITIATIVE” MEANS THE MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE.
27 10–4E–02.
28 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE IN THE CORPORATION.
29 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE INITIATIVE IS TO SUPPORT THE GROWTH OF
30 START–UP COMPANIES IN THE STATE BY:

SENATE BILL 763 3
1 (1) IDENTIFYING PROMISING COMPANIES IN THE PHASE BETWEEN
2 EARLY START–UP DEVELOPMENT AND SCALING;
3 (2) PROVIDING ACCESS TO EXPERTS IN REGULATORY PROCESSES,
4 MANUFACTURING, CLINICAL TRIALS, MARKET LAUNCHES, AND OTHER AREAS OF
5 BUSINESS;
6 (3) FACILITATING PRIVATE INVESTMENT IN COMPANIES;
7 (4) ASSISTING IN THE ACQUISITION OF INFRASTRUCTURE INCLUDING
8 OFFICE SPACE, EQUIPMENT, AND SUPPORT FOR PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT; AND
9 (5) PROVIDING TECHNICAL AND BUSINESS EXPERTISE.
10 10–4E–03.
11 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE FUND.
12 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE POSTSEED AND SERIES A
13 FUNDING TO QUALIFIED BUSINESSES IN THE STATE TO SCALE UP WITHOUT NEEDING
14 TO RELOCATE.
15 (C) THE CORPORATION SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
16 (D) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
17 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
18 (2) THE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY, AND THE
19 COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
20 (E) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
21 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
22 (2) PUBLIC AND PRIVATE INVESTMENT FUNDS;
23 (3) INTEREST EARNINGS; AND
24 (4) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
25 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
26 (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY:

4 SENATE BILL 763
1 (1) FOR THE PURPOSES DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
2 SECTION;
3 (2) FOR THE PURPOSES DESCRIBED IN § 10–4E–02 OF THIS SUBTITLE;
4 AND
5 (2) (3) TO PAY THE COSTS NECESSARY TO ADMINISTER THE
6 INITIATIVE.
7 (G) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND
8 IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
9 (2) ANY INVESTMENT EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE CREDITED
10 TO THE FUND.
11 (H) (1) THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL
12 AN APPROPRIATION OF $5,000,000 FOR THE INITIATIVE.
13 (2) THE FUNDING PROVIDED IN THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE USED TO
14 SUPPLEMENT, NOT SUPPLANT, ANY FUNDS THAT WOULD OTHERWISE BE PROVIDED
15 TO THE INITIATIVE.
16 10–4E–04.
17 (A) THE INITIATIVE SHALL CREATE A CURATED LIST OF COMPANIES IN THE
18 STATE THAT ARE BETWEEN THE START–UP AND SCALING PHASES.
19 (B) PRIORITY SHALL BE GIVEN TO COMPANIES THAT ARE:
20 (1) CURRENT OR PRIOR RECIPIENTS OF FUNDING FROM THE
21 MARYLAND INNOVATION INITIATIVE;
22 (2) CURRENT OR PRIOR RECIPIENTS OF FUNDING FROM ANY OTHER
23 PROGRAM ADMINISTERED BY THE CORPORATION; AND
24 (3) MINORITY BUSINESS ENTERPRISES DESCRIBED IN § 9–4119(A) OF
25 THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE; AND
26 (4) LOCATED IN A HIGH–NEED OR ECONOMICALLY DISTRESSED
27 GEOGRAPHIC AREA OF THE STATE AS DETERMINED BY THE CORPORATION.
28 10–4E–05.

SENATE BILL 763 5
1 THE CORPORATION MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO IMPLEMENT THIS
2 SUBTITLE.
3 Article – State Finance and Procurement
4 6–226.
5 (a) (2) (i) This paragraph does not apply in fiscal years 2024 through 2028.
6 (ii) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, and unless
7 inconsistent with a federal law, grant agreement, or other federal requirement or with the
8 terms of a gift or settlement agreement, net interest on all State money allocated by the
9 State Treasurer under this section to special funds or accounts, and otherwise entitled to
10 receive interest earnings, as accounted for by the Comptroller, shall accrue to the General
11 Fund of the State.
12 (iii) The provisions of subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph do not
13 apply to the following funds:
14 212. the Department of Social and Economic Mobility Special
15 Fund; [and]
16 213. the Population Health Improvement Fund; AND
17 214. THE MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE FUND.
18 Article – State Government
19 9–4119.
20 (a) This section applies to the following minority business enterprises:
21 (1) a publicly owned business if 1 or more minority persons own at least
22 51% of the stock of the business; or
23 (2) any other business if 1 or more minority persons own at least 50% of
24 the business.
25 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
26 October 1, 2026.

